The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, Aug. 5: The US Federal Reserve (Fed) held a key interest rate steady on Tuesday in an effort to nurse the US economy back to health without further exacerbating inflation. The decision by the Fed leaves the benchmark federal funds rate target at a low 2 per cent, where it has been since April. The Fed had reduced rates by a cumulative 3.25 percentage points since mid-September in response to a turmoil in credit markets.                             
	 Calcutta, Aug. 5: Hindustan Copper Ltd has been awarded mini-ratna (category-I) status from the government that will give it a free hand in taking decisions on capital expenditures of up to Rs 500 crore.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 5: Ranbaxy said the open offer by Daiichi Sankyo for acquiring an additional 20 per cent stake in it would commence on August 16. Pursuant to the Sebi letter dated August 4, the offer would open on August 16, instead of August 8.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 5: An empowered group of ministers has decided to continue with the export ban on foodgrains, including non-basmati rice and wheat.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 5: State-run NHPC will file a revised draft prospectus with market regulator Sebi in two days for its initial public offering.                                                                                                                                   
